ru.ifmo.rain.kokorin.implementor

Class Implementor

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.ifmo.rain.kokorin.implementor.Implementor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Impler, JarImpler

    public class Implementor
extends Object
implements Impler, JarImpler
    This class creates Impl-classes - implementations of classes and interfaces, that user provides. Class offers user
    • to create .lava files with source codes of implementations
    • to compile them and pack compiled .class into Jar-archives
    implements Impler and JarImpler
    Since:
    HW 4
    Version:
    HW 5
    Author:
    Ilya Kokorin
    See Also:
    Impler, JarImpler

    • Method Detail

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
        Main method, that will be executed. This methods starts implementation, depending on arguments from command line. If method is executed with -jar argument, implemented class will be packed in JAR-archive. Otherwise, creates .java file with source code.
        Usage:
        • java Implementor -jar <class-to-implement> <path-to-root> calls implement(Class, Path)
        • java Implementor <class-to-implement> <path-to-root> calls implementJar(Class, Path)
        Where class-to-implement defines name of the class or interface to implement, and path-to-root is a path to root, where .java or .jar files should be placed.
        Parameters:
        args - arguments for running the program from the command line.
        See Also:
        implement(Class, Path)

      • hasAccessibleConstructors

        private Optional<Constructor<?>> hasAccessibleConstructors(Class<?> token)
        Checks, if there are any constructors, that can be accessed from subclass (public, protected or package-private). If there is at least one accessible constructor, it will be saved in nonPrivateConstructor field.
        Parameters:
        token - type token, where function will search constructors.
        Returns:
        true, if and only if there is at least one constructor, that can be accessed. Otherwise, returns false.
        See Also:
        nonPrivateConstructor, Modifier.isPrivate(int), Class.getModifiers()

      • checkCorrect

        private void checkCorrect(Class<?> token)
                   throws ImplerException
        Checks, if type token can be implemented. Type token is considered incorrect, if
        • specified token is final
        • specified token is enum
        • specified token is primitive
        • specified token is array
        • specified token isn't interface and contains only private constructors
        Also, finds accessible constructor and saves it inside nonPrivateConstructor field using hasAccessibleConstructors(Class) method.
        Parameters:
        token - type token to be checked for correctness.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if given token is incorrect. Cause of incorrectness is stored inside exception object.
        See Also:
        hasAccessibleConstructors(Class), nonPrivateConstructor, ImplerException

      • printPackage

        private static void printPackage(Class<?> token,
                                 Writer writer)
                          throws IOException
        Prints name of the package of the generated class to file with source code of the generated class.
        Impl class is stored in the package with name, same to given class package's name.
        If given class isn't located in the default package, prints concatenation of strings "package " and name of the given class package name to the file with Impl class source code. If given class is located in the main package, doesn't print anything.
        Parameters:
        token - class to create implementation for. Impl class will be put to package with name, same to token's package name.
        writer - writer, associated with wile with source code of Impl class.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an Output error occurs while writing to file.
        See Also:
        Writer, Class.getPackage()

      • addMethodsToSet

        private static void addMethodsToSet(Method[] methods,
                                    Set<Implementor.MethodWrapper> set)
        Method is used to add abstract method from array of Method to Set of Implementor.MethodWrapper. Two methods are considered equal, if their signature (name and list of parameters) are equal.
        Only abstract methods are added to set.
        Implementor.MethodWrapper is used to provide the desired method equal for methods.
        Parameters:
        methods - array of methods, that should be added to set.
        set - set of Implementor.MethodWrapper, that stores methods with distinct signatures.
        See Also:
        Method, Implementor.MethodWrapper, Implementor.MethodWrapper.equals(Object), Set, Method.getModifiers(), Modifier.isAbstract(int)

      • getAbstractMethodsFromSuperclasses

        private static Set<Implementor.MethodWrapper> getAbstractMethodsFromSuperclasses(Class<?> token)
        Method is used to get Set, consists of Implementor.MethodWrapper, wrapping abstract methods from the given class superclasses. Signatures of methods, stored in set, are distinct.
        All methods in set are
        • abstract
        • declared in given class superclasses, not superinterfaces
        addMethodsToSet(Method[], Set) is used to add methods to set.
        Parameters:
        token - class, from superclasses of which methods are got.
        Returns:
        Set of Implementor.MethodWrapper, wrapping abstract methods from given class superclasses, with distinct signatures.
        See Also:
        Set, Implementor.MethodWrapper, Method, addMethodsToSet(Method[], Set), Class.getSuperclass()

      • printMethod

        private static void printMethod(Method method,
                                Writer writer)
                         throws IOException
        Prints implementation of given abstract method, using specified writer.
        Implementation consists of only one command, performing default value return.
        Implementation of method returns
        • false, if method returns boolean
        • 0, if method returns arithmetical primitive type (int, long, char, double, float, byte, short)
        • nothing, if method returns void
        • null, otherwise
        All of method's modifiers are printed before the implementation body, except
        • abstract, because method with body cannot be abstract
        • transient, because method cannot be transient
        • native, because method implementation is written in Java, not in other languages
        Parameters:
        method - abstract method to create implementation for.
        writer - writer, used to print implementation.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an Output error occurs while writing.
        See Also:
        Modifier, Method, Writer, IOException, printDeclaration(Executable, Writer)

        Prints implementations of all abstract methods, declared in given class, it's superclasses and superinterfaces, using printMethod(Method, Writer).
        All implementations are printed one-by-one, using specified writer.
        Parameters:

        writer - writer, used to print implementations.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an Output error occurs while writing.
        See Also:
        Writer, IOException, Class, getAbstractMethodsFromSuperclasses(Class), addMethodsToSet(Method[], Set), printMethod(Method, Writer)

      • implement

        public void implement(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Gets class or interface to implement and generates source code for class, implementing it.
        Output file is created in subdirectory of the given root. Output file is created in the folder, corresponding package of the given class, i.e. implementation of Collection will be placed into root/java/util/CollectionImpl.java.
        The resulting class is located in a package, whose name coincides with the name of the package, in which the given-user class is located.
        Output file contains public class, implementing given class or interface. This class has suffix Impl in classname. Output file can be compiled without errors.
        Generated class contains implementations of all abstract method, declared in given class or interface, and in all his superclasses or superinterfaces, and one public constructor, with which instances of Impl class can be created. All methods of Impl class ignore their arguments and return default value:
        • false, if method returns boolean
        • 0, if method returns arithmetical primitive type (int, long, char, double, float, byte, short)
        • nothing, if method returns void
        • null, otherwise
        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory, where to place Impl.java file. If the directory doesn't exist, it will be created.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if implementation cannot be created because
        • specified token is final
        • specified token is enum
        • specified token is primitive
        • specified token is array
        • specified token isn't interface and contains only private constructors
        • Directory for .java file cannot be created
        • If an input/output exception occurs
        NullPointerException - if either token or root is null
        See Also:
        checkCorrect(Class), Impler, ImplerException, NullPointerException, Class, Impler.implement(Class, Path)

      • implementAndCompile

        private Path implementAndCompile(Class<?> token,
                                 Path pathToTempDirectory)
                          throws ImplerException
        Creates .class file with implementation of given class.
        First, generates .java file with source code with implementation of given class, using Impler.implement(Class, Path). Source code is put in pathToTempDirectory.
        After creating source code, compiles it, using default Java compiler, returned by ToolProvider.getSystemJavaCompiler(). Compiled class is put in temp directory, with source code.
        Generated class package name is similar to given class package name.
        Parameters:
        token - class to create implementation for.
        pathToTempDirectory - path to temp directory, where source code and compiled .class file with Impl class will be located.
        Returns:
        path to compiled .class file with implementation of token class. The .class file is located in pathToTempDirectory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if
        • given class cannot be extended
        • Java compiler cannot be found
        • an input/output exception occurs
        • directories for temporary files cannot be created
        • compiler returns non-zero result code
        Since:
        HW 5
        See Also:
        JavaCompiler, ToolProvider.getSystemJavaCompiler(), implement(Class, Path)

      • implementJar

        public void implementJar(Class<?> token,
                         Path jarFile)
                  throws ImplerException
        Method gets class or interface to implement and generates .jar-archive, containing class, implementing it.
        Name and location of generated .jar-file if specified by second argument of the method.
        The resulting class is located in a package, whose name coincides with the name of the package, in which the given-user class is located.
        Output .jar-file contains compiled public class, implementing given class or interface. This class has suffix Impl in classname. Generated class contains implementations of all abstract method, declared in given class or interface, and in all his superclasses or superinterfaces, and one public constructor, with which instances of Impl class can be created. All methods of Impl class ignore their arguments and return default value:
        • false, if method returns boolean
        • 0, if method returns arithmetical primitive type (int, long, char, double, float, byte, short)
        • nothing, if method returns void
        • null, otherwise
        implement(Class, Path) is used for generating source code of Impl class.
        createJarFile(Class, Path, Path) is used for creating .jar-archive.
        Specified by:
        implementJar in interface JarImpler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        jarFile - target .jar file.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - f implementation cannot be created because
        • specified token is final
        • specified token is enum
        • specified token is primitive
        • specified token is array
        • specified token isn't interface and contains only private constructors
        • Either directory for .jar-file or .jar-file itself cannot be created
        • If an input/output exception occurs
        • If Java compiler cannot be found
        • If class compilation ends with non-zero code
        NullPointerException - if either token or jarFile is null
        Since:
        HW 5
        See Also:
        implement(Class, Path), Class, ImplerException, NullPointerException, createJarFile(Class, Path, Path), JarImpler.implementJar(Class, Path)
